docs.abstract: Two of Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez’s top aides are leaving her office after clashing with elected House members and pursuing primary challenges.
docs.snippet: Two of Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez’s top aides are leaving her office after clashing with elected House members and pursuing primary challenges.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two of Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez’s top aides who were instrumental in forging her unexpected path to victory last year are leaving Capitol Hill, less than a month after one of them ignited a firestorm by challenging Speaker Nancy Pelosi and comparing moderate House Democrats to segregationists.

headline.main: Embattled Ocasio-Cortez Aides Are Leaving Capitol Hill
headline.print_headline: Ocasio-Cortez’s Top Aides, Clashing With House Members, Will Exit Office

docs.abstract: The soldier, who was killed while fighting alongside Afghan commandos in Wardak Province, is the 17th American service member to die during combat operations this year.
docs.snippet: The soldier, who was killed while fighting alongside Afghan commandos in Wardak Province, is the 17th American service member to die during combat operations this year.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — An American Special Forces soldier was killed in eastern Afghanistan on Monday, according to Defense Department officials, a little more than a week after President Trump called off peace negotiations with the Taliban.

headline.main: U.S. Soldier Killed in Afghanistan Just Over a Week After Trump Scraps Peace Talks
headline.print_headline: U.S. Soldier Is Killed in Afghanistan, Days After Trump Scraps Peace Talks With Taliban

docs.abstract: After oil installations were blown up, President Trump seemed to suggest he was ready to strike back. Then he promised to wait, setting off criticism.
docs.snippet: After oil installations were blown up, President Trump seemed to suggest he was ready to strike back. Then he promised to wait, setting off criticism.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After oil installations were blown up in Saudi Arabia over the weekend, President Trump declared that the United States was “locked and loaded,” a phrase that seemed to suggest he was ready to strike back. But then he promised to wait for Saudi Arabia to tell him “under what terms we would proceed.”

headline.main: With Oil Under Attack, Trump’s Deference to Saudis Returns
headline.print_headline: With Oil Under Attack, Trump’s Deference to Saudis Returns to the Fore

docs.lead_paragraph: BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. — President Trump engaged in a long-distance debate over Iran with one of his closest allies on Tuesday as Republicans sought to influence the administration’s response to the attacks on oil facilities in Saudi Arabia over the weekend.

headline.main: Trump Hits Back After Ally Denounces ‘Weakness’ With Iran

docs.abstract: In a letter, the top two Democrats in Congress called on the president to expand background checks to nearly all gun buyers.
docs.snippet: In a letter, the top two Democrats in Congress called on the president to expand background checks to nearly all gun buyers.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The top two Democrats in Congress called on Sunday for President Trump to defy the National Rifle Association and get behind legislation, already passed by the House but blocked in the Senate, to expand background checks to nearly all gun buyers.

headline.main: Pelosi and Schumer, in Push for Gun Safety Legislation, Urge Trump to Defy N.R.A.
headline.print_headline: Schumer and Pelosi Urge Trump to Take Action on Guns in Letter

docs.abstract: Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s draft plan to allow the federal government to negotiate the price of hundreds of drugs will add new urgency to Washington’s effort to fight rising prescription costs.
docs.snippet: Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s draft plan to allow the federal government to negotiate the price of hundreds of drugs will add new urgency to Washington’s effort to fight rising prescription costs.
docs.lead_paragraph: A draft proposal by Speaker Nancy Pelosi would empower the federal government to negotiate lower prices for hundreds of prescription drugs, not only for Medicare but for the private market as well, injecting new urgency into Washington’s efforts to control the soaring price of pharmaceuticals.

headline.main: Pelosi Energizes Battle to Lower Drug Prices
headline.print_headline: Pelosi Adds to Developing Debate on Rising Costs of Drugs With a Proposal of Her Own

docs.abstract: Representative Henry Cuellar is one of only three House Democrats with “A” ratings from the gun lobby. Now he faces a primary challenge from the left.
docs.snippet: Representative Henry Cuellar is one of only three House Democrats with “A” ratings from the gun lobby. Now he faces a primary challenge from the left.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAREDO, Tex. — In this gun-friendly border city, where Tuesdays are “ladies’ nights” at the shooting range and pistols in hip holsters are a common sight, Representative Henry Cuellar is a proud defender of the Second Amendment, the lone House Democrat from Texas with an “A” rating from the National Rifle Association.

headline.main: In Texas, a Lone House Democrat Has an ‘A’ Rating From the N.R.A. Can He Survive?
headline.print_headline: A Texas Democrat With the N.R.A.’s ‘A’ Rating. For Now.

docs.abstract: A survey of military operations seems to indicate that, at best, the president is exaggerating the pace of current operations, even if they have increased in recent weeks.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Since the Afghan peace talks collapsed last weekend, President Trump has repeatedly said that the American military was striking the Taliban harder than it has for a decade, or even since the start of the war in 2001.

headline.main: Fact-Checking Trump’s Statements on Increased Military Strikes in Afghanistan
headline.print_headline: Trump Claims Largest Taliban Toll in 10 Years. Is He Right?

docs.abstract: The panel set rules to explore possible impeachment of President Trump, hoping to show courts and impatient Democrats that it is building a case.
docs.snippet: The panel set rules to explore possible impeachment of President Trump, hoping to show courts and impatient Democrats that it is building a case.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House Judiciary Committee on Thursday took its first recorded vote to press forward with a possible impeachment of President Trump, putting aside Democrats’ internal divisions for the time being in a bid to strengthen its hand in investigating whether he committed high crimes and misdemeanors.

headline.main: House Judiciary Committee Inches Toward Impeachment
headline.print_headline: Inching Toward Impeachment, House Judiciary Committee Sets Rules

docs.abstract: The House passed a provision that would require the president to get Congress’s approval before authorizing military force against Iran.
docs.snippet: The House passed a provision that would require the president to get Congress’s approval before authorizing military force against Iran.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House gave final approval Friday to a defense bill that would put a liberal stamp on military policy by shackling President Trump’s ability to wage war in Iran and Yemen, restricting the use of military funds at the southwestern border and returning transgender troops to the armed forces.

headline.main: House Passes $733 Billion Defense Bill Checking Trump’s War Powers
headline.print_headline: House Lawmakers, Voting Along Party Lines, Pass $733 Billion Defense Bill
